re – that would restore the nation to spiritual and political health. The Fascists, for their part, specifically promoted palingenesis, which is to say the spiritual rebirth of the nation.  The book closes with a long epilogue, in which Ramet defends liberal democracy, highlighting its strengths and advantages. In this chapter, the author identifies five key choke points, which would-be authoritarians typically seek to control, subvert, or instrumentalize: electoral rules, the judiciary, the media, hate speech, and surveillance, and looks at the cases of Viktor Orbán’s Hungary, Jarosław Kaczyński’s Poland, and Donald Trump’s United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAnarchismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aCollectivismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aDemocracyzEuropey20th century. 0aFascismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismzEuropexHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aAnarchism, Communism, Democracy, Fascism, Illiberalism, Liberalism, Nazism, Political theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2019z978311078051240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633863107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633863107/original  a978-3-11-078051-2  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK